commit.message:
Require transformers >= 0.6.1.0 with GHC-9.9

Then we can define Traversable1 instances for Reverse, Backwards
etc. unconditionally

Re-export Foldable1/Bifoldable from base, migrate instances

This patch:

* Re-exports the `Foldable1` and `Bifoldable` classes from `base` or
  `foldable-classes-compat`, depending on which version of `base` is being
  used.
* Migrates the `Foldable1` and `Bifoldable1` instances to their respective
  downstream packages. I have bumped the lower version bounds on `bifunctors`
  and `tagged` to ensure that they always provide these instances.
* Bump primary version number to 6. This is done out of an abundance of caution
  to warn users that they may need to migrate existing code that defines
  `Foldable1` instances without implementations of `foldMap1`. See the
  `CHANGELOG` entry for the full details.

Fixes #130.

Drop support for pre-8.0 GHCs

This is a prerequisite for later changes planned in #130, where we will need to
bump the lower version bounds on `bifunctors` to bring in the changes from
ekmett/bifunctors#111.

commit.message:
Adapt to (~) becoming a type operator

`(~)` now requires `TypeOperators` in GHC 9.4 (see
https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/wikis/migration/9.4?version_id=503a517b7238e8bac3dd588f32e234bf74b17097#-is-now-a-type-operator)
to build without warnings.
Replace Bind constraints with Functor for Plus instances where possible
Replace Bind constraints with Functor for Alt instances where possible

commit.message:
Instances for CPS Writer and RWST (improved) (#119)

* Add instances for CPS transformers.

Conditionalized on transformers >= 0.5.6.

Unfortunately, the operations on CPS transformers are a bit
overconstrained (e.g., Monoid instead of Semigroup), so the instances are
correspondingly more constrained than the Lazy and Strict ones.

* Less constrained CPS instances, sinces, changelog

* Move coercions to internal module

* Repair Trustworthy on old GHCs

Co-authored-by: Greg Pfeil <greg@technomadic.org>

commit.message:
Improve performance of NonEmpty functions (#88)

Currently, the foldMap1 and traverse1 functions for NonEmpty make a lot of
unnecessary intermediate lists. Refactor the code to avoid all such
intermediate lists for foldMap1, and half of them for traverse1 (removing
the remaining half for traverse1 would be more complicated and probably
require a new datatype, so I'll save it for a later PR.)

commit.message:
Guard Option instances behind CPP

This is needed to make `semigroupoids` build on GHC 9.2. See
https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/wikis/migration/9.2?version_id=318ba54dba47ed35d89648e027104cf766a63410#option-removed-from-datasemigroup.
